    {
      "id": "RQ-0066",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Experiment with local source lookup for visible UI elements",
      "priority": "low",
      "tags": [
        "agent-browser",
        "source-lookup",
        "react",
        "experiment"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Mapping UI elements back to source could be powerful for debugging local apps, but it is higher complexity and should start from existing React inspection/source-map surfaces.",
        "The wrapper must report uncertainty clearly and avoid pretending every DOM node maps cleanly to a file."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Inventory what the current React inspection, DOM metadata, sourcemaps, and local workspace context can reliably expose for a selected element.",
        "Prototype an opt-in lookup that reports candidate component/file locations with confidence and evidence, not a single guaranteed answer.",
        "Gate the feature behind explicit inputs and clear unsupported-state categories when React DevTools or sourcemaps are unavailable.",
        "Document limitations and decide from benchmark/dogfood evidence whether to promote beyond experiment."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Infer and queue local-app source lookup experiment from the user's ABN task list.",
      "created_at": "2026-05-13T13:33:42.731677000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-13T13:40:06.107090000Z",
      "depends_on": [
