    {
      "id": "RQ-0068",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Decide whether repeated browser jobs should become reusable recipes",
      "priority": "low",
      "tags": [
        "agent-browser",
        "recipes",
        "jobs",
        "product-decision"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "docs",
        "extensions/agent-browser",
        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Reusable recipes are only valuable if benchmark or dogfood data shows repeated job shapes that agents should not have to re-specify.",
        "Adding a recipe layer too early risks another source of truth for workflows."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Analyze benchmark, QA, and dogfood usage after job mode exists to identify repeated job shapes and failure-prone sequences.",
        "If recipes are justified, define a small recipe format with ownership, docs, versioning, and clear boundaries from prompt guidance and tests.",
        "If not justified, document the decision and keep examples as docs rather than executable recipe state.",
        "Add verification only for adopted recipes, avoiding speculative framework code."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Infer and queue reusable browser recipe decision from the user's ABN task list.",
